This repetition creates anomalies.

1. Update Anomaly
Definition

An Update Anomaly occurs when the same data exists in multiple rows and must be updated everywhere.

If one copy is not updated, the database becomes inconsistent.

Example

Suppose Teacher Sharma changes his phone number.

Old number

9999

New number

7777

Now you have to update

Row 1

Row 2

Row 3

Suppose you update only two rows.

Student	Teacher	Phone
Rahul	Sharma	7777
Amit	Sharma	7777
Priya	Sharma	9999

Now what is Sharma's phone number?

7777 ?

or

9999 ?

Nobody knows.

Database has become inconsistent.

This is called

Update Anomaly
Real Life Example

Imagine a company.

Employee records

Employee	Department	Manager
A	HR	Rohit
B	HR	Rohit
C	HR	Rohit

Manager changes from Rohit to Mohit.

You must update all rows.

If one row still says Rohit,

Database becomes incorrect.

Another Example

Amazon stores warehouse address.

Product	Warehouse
Laptop	Delhi
Mouse	Delhi
Keyboard	Delhi

Warehouse shifts to Noida.

Need to update every row.

Forget one row.

Now some products are in Delhi.

Some are in Noida.

Wrong information.

Interview Definition

Update anomaly occurs when changing one piece of information requires multiple updates, and failure to update all copies causes inconsistent data.

2. Insertion Anomaly
Definition

Insertion anomaly occurs when you cannot insert information because some unrelated information is missing.

Example

Suppose a new teacher joins.

Teacher

Mr. Verma

Phone

6666

Course

AI

But

No student has enrolled yet.

Your table is

Student	Course	Teacher

How will you insert

Teacher = Verma

There is no Student ID.

No Student Name.

No Student record.

You cannot insert the teacher.

Even though teacher exists.

Why?

Because your table mixes

Student data

Teacher data

Course data

all together.

This is

Insertion Anomaly
Real Life Example

Hospital Database

Patient	Doctor
Rahul	Dr. A
Amit	Dr. A

New doctor joins.

No patients yet.

Can you insert doctor?

No.

Because patient columns are compulsory.

